<doc title="Examining changes">
    <section>
        <p>
            Besides the status icons in front of files in the Solution Explorer, 
            Ankh gives you a more detailed view of the changes made to files. 
            This is done with the ‘Diff’ command. 
        </p>
        <br/><br/><br/>
        <b>How to diff files:</b>
        <p>
            <img src="../../img/diff_file.png" align="left" />
            <list>
                <item><b>1.</b> Shows which files that has been diff'ed.</item>
                <item><b>2.</b> Shows which revision the file is beeing diff'ed against.</item>
                <item><b>3.</b> Shows linenumber and position of a section tha differs.</item>
                <item><b>4.</b> '+' indicates added text fragment. </item>
                <item><b>5.</b> '-' indicates removed text fragment. </item>
            </list>
            <br clear="all"/>
        </p>

    </section>   
